IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Provide quality and compassionate primary and preventive medical dental and pharmaceutical services to Central Florida economically and culturally diverse communities
IRS990.MissionDescription: Provide quality and compassionate primary and preventive medical dental and pharmaceutical services to Central Florida economically and culturally diverse communities
IRS990.Description: Medical services - CHC expands over six communities and has ten medical sites four pharmacies and five dental sites CHC provided primary medical dental and pharmaceutical services to 48703 patients last year with 148042 visits including 8587 dental patients in 24898 dental visits The pharmacies filled over 109000 prescriptions CHC received donated use of facilities of 317405

Activity2.Description: Dental services - CHC provided comprehensive dental services to both adults and pediatric patients 8587 patients were seen last year including 24898 dental visits Dental services provided include dentures bridges fillings periodontial servi ces children services and dental hygiene The dental services received donated use of facilities of 32820

Activity3.Description: Pharmacy services - CHC receives 340b pricing which allows affordable prescriptions to patients Over 109000 prescriptions were filled during the year at four sites Over 850000 worth of prescriptions were dispensed to patients under the Share t he Care program and several Prescription Assistance Programs

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 01. Form 990 governing body review (Part VI, line 11)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Form 990 will be reviewed in detail annually by the Finance Committee and approved by the full board of directors

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 02. Conflict of interest policy compliance (Part VI, line 12c)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: On an annual basis everyone is asked to review the conflict of interest policy and complete if necessary

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: See the process described in line 15b

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 04. Other officer or key employee compensation (Part VI, line 15b
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Comparative data is utilized among HFMA NACHC FACHC and national independent surveys and applied according to size and revenue for other not-for-profit organizations

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: 05. Governing documents, etc, available to public (Part VI, line 19)
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Governing document conflict of interest policy and financial statements are made available to the public upon written request
